	<a href="http://www6.tomshardware.com/storage/20000821/">Tom's Hardware Guide Mass Storage: Fastest IDE Hard Drive Ever: IBM Deskstar 75GXP - IBM DTLA-307030</a>.&nbsp; Exploring the latest specifications on memory and disk drives.&nbsp; I figure to find monster drives for use on mainframes, but that isn't apparently what happens.&nbsp; Instead, for non-removable drives, we find arrays of low-form factor, small drives of the same kind that go into PCs.&nbsp; I want to find out how sound that observation is.<br>
	<span class="byline">posted by Dennis at <a href="#86351897">Friday, December 20, 2002</a></span></div>
<br>
  <!-- 2002-11-08 Change date format to yyyy-mm-dd and bookmark it 
