	<div class="posts">
	<a name="86339996">&nbsp;</a><br>
	<h1>Computer Technology</h1><h2>Storage Systems</h2><h3>Optimizing high-capacity disk storage systems</h3><<a href="http://www.almaden.ibm.com/StorageSystems/performance/ALIS/index.shtml">IBM Research | ALIS at Almaden</a>.&nbsp; ALIS is Automatic Locality-Improving Storage.&nbsp; This page gives a handy summary of the situation being faced as the result of processor improvements outpacing that for storage.&nbsp; Locality improvement is something that products like Speed Disk provide on PCs, and some of the current optimizers use access information provided by the operating system.&nbsp; The IBM work is intended to deal with the issues at the mainframe and very-high-performance storage end.&nbsp; A number of papers are provided on a link page.<br>
	<span class="byline">posted by Dennis at <a href="#86339996">Friday, December 20, 2002</a></span></div>
<br>
